# AI Career Guidance System - Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- **Backend**: Python 3.10+, Flask 3.x
- **Database**: MySQL with flask-mysqldb (DictCursor)
- **Auth**: Flask-Login + Flask-Bcrypt
- **Frontend**: Jinja2 templates, vanilla CSS/JS, Font Awesome icons

## Project Structure
```
ai-career/
├── app/
│   ├── __init__.py          # Flask app factory
│   ├── models.py            # User model + DB helpers
│   ├── routes/              # Blueprint route handlers
│   │   ├── main.py          # Public pages (home, about, contact)
│   │   ├── auth.py          # Login, register, logout
│   │   ├── admin.py         # Admin-only dashboard & management
│   │   └── career.py        # Assessments, results, explore
│   ├── templates/           # Jinja2 HTML templates
│   └── static/              # CSS, JS, images
├── config.py                # App configuration
├── database.sql             # MySQL schema + seed data
├── run.py                   # Entry point
└── requirements.txt
```

## Conventions
- Use Flask Blueprints for route organization
- Raw SQL queries via `mysql.connection.cursor()` (no ORM)
- All routes returning HTML use `render_template()`
- Protect routes with `@login_required` and `@admin_required`
- Flash messages use categories: success, danger, warning, info
- CSS uses custom properties (variables) defined in `:root`

## Database
- MySQL database name: `ai_career_guidance`
- Admin credentials: username `admin`, password `admin`
- Password hashing: bcrypt via Flask-Bcrypt
- All queries use parameterized `%s` placeholders (never f-strings)
